  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2021-02-03",
    "date": "2021-03-11T15:56:02Z",
    "text": "States Afforded Funding Extensions To Oppose Driving Recklessly In Vehicular Engagements Act or the SAFE TO DRIVE Act\n\nThis bill requires the Department of Transportation to use up to 25% of the amounts available for national priority safety program grants to award grants to any state that certifies it\u00a0has enacted a distracted driving statute that (1) is applicable to drivers of all ages, (2) makes a violation of the statute a primary offense, and (3) prohibits texting or all non-navigational viewing of a personal wireless communications device."
  },
